# Candidate Transformer

Multi-source candidate data transformer for the Eightfold Engineering Internship assignment.

The project ingests CSV, ATS JSON, resume PDF text, GitHub profile JSON, and recruiter notes, then normalizes and merges candidate records into a validated canonical JSON document with confidence and provenance.

## Architecture

```mermaid
flowchart TD
  A[Source Detection] --> B[Parser]
  B --> C[Canonical Partial Candidate]
  C --> D[Normalization]
  D --> E[ML Matching]
  E --> F[Conflict Resolution]
  F --> G[Confidence]
  G --> H[Provenance]
  H --> I[Projection]
  I --> J[JSON Schema Validation]
  J --> K[Output]
```

## Run

```bash
python -m pip install -r requirements-dev.txt
python main.py --csv examples/recruiter.csv --ats-json examples/ats.json --notes examples/notes.txt --config config/default_projection.json
```

The default embedding backend is deterministic and lightweight. To enable pretrained SentenceTransformer embeddings:

```bash
python -m pip install -r requirements-ml.txt
set CANDIDATE_TRANSFORMER_EMBEDDING_BACKEND=sentence-transformer
```

Start the API:

```bash
uvicorn candidate_transformer.api.app:create_app --factory --reload
```

Docker:

```bash
docker compose up --build
```

Swagger docs are available at `http://localhost:8000/docs`.

## Design Principles

- Clean architecture: API and CLI are adapters over the same application pipeline.
- Deterministic ML: pretrained SentenceTransformer support is available, with a deterministic hash backend for tests and offline deployments.
- Explainability: confidence scores include field-level explanations.
- Runtime projection: field selection, renaming, missing-value policy, confidence, and provenance are configurable without code changes.
- Validation-first output: every API and CLI result is checked against JSON Schema.

## Development

```bash
make install-dev
make format
make lint
make typecheck
make security
make test
```
